text: Cheyenne is the capital and largest city of Wyoming, a state of the United States of America. At the time of the 2020 census, there were 65,132 living in Cheyenne. It is the county seat of Laramie County. Cheyenne was founded in 1867. The current mayor of Cheyenne is Patrick Collins. == References == == Other websites == * City of Cheyenne official * Category:County seats in Wyoming Category:State capitals in the United States Category:1867 establishments in the United States Category:1860s establishments in Wyoming Territory
